   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-RDP (Washington) _ With the president's impeachment now
before the Senate, senators from both parties pledged to restore
civility to the process but quickly divided largely along party
lines over whether President Clinton must face a trial or whether a
quick censure deal could be negotiated. By Alison Mitchell. (With a
photo and a graphic on the impeachment vote totals by district.)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-CLINTON (Washington) _ The White House strategy,
developments. By John M. Broder and James Bennet.
</P>
<P>
