<HEADLINE>
OF BOBBY, TERRY AND MIKE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Stuff we hear versus stuff we can't believe:
</P>
<P>
   Terry Donahue has his biggest promoter _ himself _ selling Bobby
Beathard on the idea about what a neat fit it would be for him to
direct the San Diego Chargers Symphony Football Team. TD just
bought a newly remodeled home on Balboa Island. If it gets him to
give up on this TV career, we're all for it....
</P>
<P>
   Karl Malone's days at AM-1150 are done. ``On vacation'' from the
show until after the first of the year is how he and Vic ``I'm More
Annoying than Someone Popping Bubble Wrap'' Jacobs spinned it last
Wednesday, after splashing through their ``peace on earth, goodwill
toward men'' speeches. But since the senseless station gave Steve
Edwards and Eric Tracy some quality time in the afternoons this
week, and Malone has been phoning it in from his squirrel hunting
trips in Arkansas lately, it doesn't make sense to keep the charade
going any longer. The novelty has done worn off. True, hiring him
made no sense in the first place, so this could be much ado about
nothing. Or, as Malone said last week when trying to use that
phrase, ``A lot have been made to do about nothing''...
</P>
<P>
   Bob Arum wants to put up a coupla mil on the table to get MC
Shaq Daddy into the square ring to pound or be pounded on by
Butterbean. Arum musta been inspired by Shaq's slapfight with
Utah's Greg Ostertag last... whenever there was an NBA season...
</P>
<P>
   Michael Jordan's courtship with Vanna White. (begin
ital)Huh?(end ital) The headline in the Dec. 22 Globe: ``Vanna &AMP;
Michael Jordan caught in SEX TAPE SCANDAL.'' (begin ital)MJ buying
an illegal vowel?(end ital) The story turns out that a company
specializing in Internet celebrity porn has put out a videotape
with actors re-creating the ``alleged love romps'' of a couple
dozen stars. Jordan's stunt double and White's look-alike are in
two separate scenes, neither involving Pat Sajak....
</P>
<P>
   Disney won't buy any more teams. Michael Eisner told the Calgary
Sun recently that the Magic Kingdom's threat to professional sports
ends with its current fiefdom. And, no, Disney won't buy any teams
in Canada, either. ``I can't see why we would want teams outside
the U.S.... It would just make us unpopular,'' he said, forgetting
to use the word ``more'' before that final adjective....
</P>
<P>
   Frank Gifford's TV career may be going clockwise down the
commode, but his marriage is as strong as it's ever been. The cover
of the Jan. '99 Good Housekeeping touts a story on ``The New Kathie
Lee Gifford: The amazing story of what she did for Frank _ and how
tough love and her sense of humor are healing their marriage.''
</P>
<P>
   So those are tears of (begin ital)joy(end ital) in Frank's eyes,
folks....
</P>
<P>
   Despite a late run from President Clinton, Monica Lewinsky and
Kenneth Starr, Time magazine goes and decides that Mark McGwire is
its Hero (Not To Be Confused with Newsmaker) of the Year. Which
forces us to believe that it's just another synergetic marketing
scheme dreamed up by the folks over at Time Inc.'s Sports
Illustrated...
</P>
<P>
   And no one needs to see McGwire and/or Sammy Sosa in togas....
</P>
<P>
   And Bill Parcells can stop worrying about that SI cover jinx....
</P>
<P>
   Political turmoil like this makes us long for when the NCAA used
to have the (Im)Peach Bowl, the Independence Bowl and the Freedom
Bowl. 'Cause we're damn proud to be an American right now, right
Billy Bob?...
</P>
<P>
   Dave Kingman, who never hit 50 home runs, turns 50 today.
Tuesday, Steve Garvey hits the mid-century mark....
</P>
<P>
   Today would have also been Flo Jo's 39th birthday....
</P>
<P>
   The National Thoroughbred Racing Association has hired actor Rip
Torn _ Artie from ``The Larry Sanders Show'' _ for its newest ad
campaign that will emphasize the wagering side of the sport.
Ironically, ripped and torn is how our betting tickets usually end
up.... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tom Hoffarth can be reached at sptmediaaol.com or (818)
713-3661.!end! &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
